Chapter 4 defined geospatial abduction problems (GAPs) and studied a version of the problem where the adversary (the ‚Äúbad guy‚Äù or the entity that wishes
to evade detection) does not reason about the agent (the ‚Äúgood guy‚Äù or the entity
