bound [‚Ñì, u] such that K entails F : t : [‚Ñì, u]. As our operator is only sound, we
do not guarantee that the bounds [‚Ñì, u] are the tightest possible. Further, even if
we could obtain the tightest probability bounds possible, there is no guarantee on
how close ‚Ñì is to u. Hence, if we obtain the probability bounds [0.4, 0.7], what can
