5. Alternate update rules
Broom et al. (2010a) studied evolutionary dynamics for general
games on several special graph structures: the star, the circle, and
the complete graph under a birth‚Äìdeath update process (speciÔ¨Åcally the invasion process, see Section 5) while placing an emphasis
on the speed of the evolutionary process in their analysis. At each
time step, the Ô¨Åtness of an individual is assumed to be the average of
the payoffs of games against all its neighbors. The authors analyze
and derive exact solutions for the Ô¨Åxation probability of mutants,
the mean time to absorption and the Ô¨Åxation time of mutants on the
