constants.
The next component of the language is a set of predicate symbols. Each predicate symbol
has an arity bounded by a constant value; the EM and AM use separate sets of predicate symbols, denoted with PEM , PAM , respectively ‚Äî the two models can, however, share variables
and constants.
As usual, a term is composed of either a variable or a constant. Given terms t1 , ..., tn and
