Facts (Œò) are ground literals representing atomic information or its negation, using strong
negation ‚Äú¬¨‚Äù. Note that all of the literals in our framework must be formed with a predicate
from the set PAM . Note that information in the form of facts cannot be contradicted. We will
use the notation [Œò] to denote the set of all possible facts.

Strict rules (Œ©) represent non-defeasible cause-and-effect information that resembles an
